    "created_at": "2017-03-21T21:54:49Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-21T21:55:29Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I agree that this should be exposed on the client side (it is in C and C++). However, by the time it is populated and it is too late to do any checks as the call has basically been made. The server cert validation is done by the inner logic of gRPC in the handling of the TLS protocol (according to HTTPS semantics in this case) without giving the application the opportunity to change the behavior except for some very limited use cases limited to testing such as the SSL_TARGET_NAME_OVERRIDE and it is probably safer this way.\r\nHowever logging of the certs used on the server from the client is a good use case for such an API."
  },
