    "created_at": "2017-03-22T19:15:46Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-22T19:15:46Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Would it be possible to modify the handling of the internal TLS handshake to allow clients to inspect/validate server certificates before continuing with the request?\r\n\r\nFrom a security perspective, it would be beneficial for a client to be able to validate a servers certificate public key (fingerprint) to prevent MITM attacks. I realize that mutual TLS could be used, but that adds the overhead of key management, and is not suitable for all deployments."
  },
