    "created_at": "2017-03-22T22:41:02Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-03-22T22:41:02Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "We *could* add a certificate pinning option if there is a high demand for it. However, I don't like it too much since pinning is fragile (what happens if the key for a given domain is rotated for valid reasons). [Certificate transparency](https://www.certificate-transparency.org/) is a much better option for protecting against CAs that issue certs for domains they should not issue certs for. I can see a future where we have a plugin to support certificate transparency on the validation path.\r\n\r\nOpening the validation to application code is dangerous because this is not a well understood topic and will lead to applications not doing the right thing. E.g. \"My test certificate does not work because it's hosted on localhost: let me hack a custom validator that will be a no-op so that my tests pass. Oh, this shipped into production.... ooops...\"."
  },
