    "updated_at": "2017-03-23T12:20:22Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I understand what you're saying, but I don't agree that grpc should be responsible for trying to protect developers from such mistakes. Preventing developers from _improving_ security only to eliminate the risk that some developers accidentally reduce security seems like a poor trade off.\r\n\r\nBeing able to write plugins for the certificate validation path would be very useful. In terms of protecting developers, providing pre-defined plugins (such as certificate transparency) would be great and reduce the probability of developer mistakes."
